The paper discusses the Workshop on Sustainable Software for Science, which focuses on promoting sustainable research software. The topics covered in the workshop include best practices, careers, learning, and credit, which are all related to software engineering (cs.SE). The workshop also covers the use of software in scientific research, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the Code of Conduct, which is related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the demos and lightning talks presented during the workshop, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL).
